oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Lt. Col. J.Y. Kinsall standing on a boat
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Lt. Col. J.Y. Kinsall. He is wearing an United States Army Air Force uniform and is standing on a boat.

After the attack on Pearl Harbor, Kinsall was transferred in 1942 to the Miami Beach Training Center in Miami, Florida from Randolph Air Force Base in San Antonio, Texas. In Miami, he became a Second Lieutenant officer and as an assistant adjutant, he helped set up the Officers Candidate School to train the "90 Day Wonders." This was a school set up for the purpose of quickly training officers within 90 days for WWII.
